<div id="banner">
	<h1>Saddam&#8217;s Simple Life</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Now that Saddam has been captured, all the television networks are looking for a way to cash in. Conventional wisdom is that a trial will be way to boring, so here are some alternate proposals that have been floated:</p>

<p>FOX - <strong>The Simple Life</strong>: Watch as the former dictator patronizingly dismisses American customs like free speech, occasionally non-rigged voting, and working at a fast food restaurant.</p>

<p>NBC - <strong>Fear Factor</strong>: Watch Saddam eat bugs. Duh.</p>

<p>ABC - <strong>Extreme Makeover</strong>: Saddam gives tips on how to disguise your self. (Tip 1: Don&#8217;t shave.)</p>

<p>CBS - <strong>Survivor</strong>: How long can Saddam last on a desert island, as his cronies are voted off one by one?</p>

<p>PBS - <strong>Charlie Rose</strong>: A probing in-depth interview with the former dictator.</p>

<p>Will any of these get picked up? Stay tuned.</p>

<p class="posted">posted December 21, 2003 12:43 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_tv">TV</a>)  <a href="001099" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

